cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is about computer vision and machine learning, specifically about generating scene graphs from images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and attention mechanisms, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as image captioning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
